Reasoning: The paper discusses circuits based on Josephson junctions and mutual inductors that act as dendrites, processing signals from synapses receiving single-photon communication events with superconducting detectors. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Emerging Technologies (cs.ET) or Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper discusses simulations of circuits performing basic temporal filtering, logical operations, and nonlinear transfer functions, which could also place it in the sub-categories of Embedded Systems (cs.ES) or Computational Complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper discusses how the synaptic signal from a single-photon can fan out locally in the electronic domain to enable the dendrites of the receiving neuron to process a photonic synapse event or pulse train in multiple different ways simultaneously, which could also place it in the sub-category of Emerging Technologies (cs.ET).
